         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/11/62 ¶ Dear Professor. ¶  ¶ By this mail I have forwarded to you the manuscript of the record on the plants of F Gregorys North West Australian Expedition, ¶  also the last 5 No of my fragmenta, i...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">62.11.24a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Balfour</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh, J. H. Balfour correspondence, vol. X, f. 266.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24/11/62</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Professor.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>By this mail I have forwarded to you the manuscript of the record on the plants of F Gregorys North West Australian Expedition,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B63.13.03.</p>
               </note> also the last 5 No of my fragmenta, in which some of these plants are described. I have not sent the plates, as they would be crushed by being sent by bookpost, but they can &amp; will be sent at a later date, as I have to send you soon seeds &amp; dried plants by sailing vessel &amp; the continuations of my works.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I beg to enclose a few seeds fresh collected of the remarkable <name key="Cathartocarpus%20Brewsteri">Cathartocarpus Brewsteri</name> from the Burdekin. It is a noble &amp; most handsome tree &amp; thus well worthy of bearing the name of the Veteran Savant of your city, who, I believe, is not aware of my having paid him this slight token of respect some years since.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">C. Brewsteri </seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was described in B59.04.04, p. 110.</p>
               </note> The species is very singular for the spherical nodes, which are born<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">borne?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>by the lower filaments.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The enclosed paragraph is a copy of a letter which I received from your energetic and ingenious pupil Dr<seg style="font-size: 10pt; "> </seg>Kirk.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Probably the letter published in the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>,<seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>21 November 1862, p. 7, col. 3. See J. Kirk to M, 4 May 1862.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever most regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Can I do anything for the R.S. of Edinburgh</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cathartocarpus%20Brewsteri">Cathartocarpus Brewsteri</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
